Male Gametophyte The Pollen Grain
The male gametophyte develops and reaches maturity in an immature anther In a plants male reproductive
organs development of pollen takes place in a structure known as the microsporangium Figure 326 The
microsporangia which are usually bilobed are pollen sacs in which the microspores develop into pollen grains
These are found in the anther which is at the end of the stamenthe long filament that supports the anther
